7.1.6 - M365SR06: Unrestricted Access to External M365 Tenancies
ISM controls:
•	Control: 1511; Revision: 2; Updated: Dec-22; Applicability: All; OS: All (Preventing unauthorised data exfiltration via cloud services)
•	Control: 1537; Revision: 1; Updated: Sep-22; Applicability: All; OS: All (Restricting user access to cloud service settings and data)
•	Control: 0846; Revision: 6; Updated: Jun-21; Applicability: All; OS: All (Authorising and restricting access to data and applications)
________________________________________
Current Risk
End-users can login to tenants other than the agency creating the possibility for a user to transfer information from within *.ga.gov.au to an external M365 tenant, compromising the confidentiality of agency information.
Risk Assessment:
Risk Likelihood	x	Risk Consequence	=	Risk Rating
LIKELY	x	MODERATE	=	HIGH
________________________________________
Recommendations:
1.	Implement Tenant Restrictions: Configure Tenant Restrictions (v2) within Entra ID and at the network egress layer to ensure users can only authenticate to the agency's approved tenant list.
2.	Enforce Managed Device Compliance: Use Conditional Access to prevent logins to any M365 tenancy from non-compliant or unmanaged agency devices.
3.	Cross-Tenant Access Settings: Strictly define Cross-Tenant Access Settings in Entra ID to block all inbound and outbound B2B collaboration by default, except for verified government partners.
- Treatment #1
•	Network Header Injection: Configure the agency’s secure web gateway or firewall to inject the Restrict-Access-To-Tenants and Restrict-Access-Context headers into outgoing traffic to Microsoft login services.
•	Conditional Access Policy Update: Implement a policy that blocks M365 application access if the device state is "Unmanaged," preventing users from bypassing restrictions on personal hardware.
•	Monitoring Exfiltration Signals: Enable and monitor Microsoft Defender for Cloud Apps (CASB) alerts for anomalous data movements between the agency tenancy and external personal or third-party storage.
________________________________________
Residual risk outcome if recommendation is implemented.
By enforcing tenant-level boundaries at both the identity and network layers, the technical path for data exfiltration to personal or external M365 environments is effectively closed. While a determined insider may seek other methods, the likelihood of a successful transfer via standard M365 login flows is reduced to "Unlikely."
Risk Likelihood	x	Risk Consequence	=	Risk Rating
UNLIKELY	x	MODERATE	=	MEDIUM

